title: BGP Route Flapping After IOS-XR 7.3.2 Upgrade
symptoms: BGP neighbors cycling Active/Idle every 30 seconds
TCP RST packets observed in packet capture
BGP table incomplete on affected routers
root_cause: GRE tunnel overhead reducing effective TCP MSS below BGP update size
solution_steps: Configure: ip tcp mss 1380 on tunnel interfaces
Verify: show tcp brief | include MSS

title: EVPN-VXLAN Forwarding Loop in Multi-Tenant DC Fabric
root_cause: Duplicate MAC advertisement due to inconsistent RT import/export configuration
solution_steps: Standardize RT values across all tenant VRFs
Clear BGP EVPN neighbors to refresh advertisements

title: SRv6 Micro-Loop During Link Failure in Service Provider Core
root_cause: Sub-optimal SRv6 path computation during topology change without TI-LFA protection
solution_steps: Tune ISIS convergence timers for faster reconvergence

title: LACP Flapping on QFX5100 After Junos 18.4R3 Upgrade
symptoms: ae0 interface flapping every few minutes
Traffic switching between member links unexpectedly
initial_troubleshooting: show system processes extensive | match lacp
root_cause: LACP timer mismatch between fast (1s) and slow (30s) modes after upgrade
solution_steps: Set consistent LACP timers on both sides
Configure lacp periodic fast on all member interfaces

junos: set interfaces ae0 aggregated-ether-options lacp active
set interfaces ae0 aggregated-ether-options lacp periodic fast

title: BGP Route Hijacking Detection and Mitigation in Enterprise
symptoms: Traffic being routed through unexpected AS path
Latency increased by 200ms for specific prefixes
Security team alerts on traffic anomalies
solution_narrative:
Found that a misconfigured BGP filter was accepting more specific routes
                from an upstream provider. The issue was caused by:
                
                1. Missing prefix-list validation
                2. No RPKI validation enabled
                3. No route flap dampening
                
                Fixed by implementing proper route filtering and RPKI.
lessons_learned: Always validate prefix announcements with RPKI

title: Memory Leak in BGP Process on ASR9000 with IOS-XR 7.3.x
symptoms: BGP process memory usage increasing over time
bgp_speaker process may crash after 72+ hours
workaround: Restart bgp process every 48 hours via cron
Limit BGP table size with maximum-prefix
